00:01:48.840 --> 00:01:53.350
and we visited the Jewish
cemetery which is here.

00:01:53.350 --> 00:01:55.830
The Jewish cemetery
was a very profound,

00:01:55.830 --> 00:01:59.730
very sacred feeling sort
of space, but there was one

00:01:59.730 --> 00:02:02.460
of the gravestones in
particular that caught my eye.

00:02:02.460 --> 00:02:04.580
It was this one.

00:02:04.580 --> 00:02:07.660
Now as you look at it
carefully, you're going to see

00:02:07.660 --> 00:02:12.530
that one thing is
different from the others.

00:02:12.530 --> 00:02:14.930
Do you see it?

00:02:14.930 --> 00:02:17.330
Let me point it out.

00:02:17.330 --> 00:02:18.630
Right here.

00:02:18.630 --> 00:02:19.930
All right?

00:02:19.930 --> 00:02:24.520
Do you see a different
death date there?

00:02:24.520 --> 00:02:28.150
Rafael Goldberg [assumed
spelling] went by the name

00:02:28.150 --> 00:02:31.030
of Eugenis [assumed spelling]
[inaudible] which I'm going

00:02:31.030 --> 00:02:32.500
to slaughter the pronunciation.

00:02:32.500 --> 00:02:33.860
I'm very sorry.

00:02:33.860 --> 00:02:37.090
He was the oldest
child in the family.

00:02:37.090 --> 00:02:43.080
Rafael was Jewish, but
forged papers to pass

00:02:43.080 --> 00:02:47.310
as a Polish Christian in
order to survive the war.

00:02:47.310 --> 00:02:50.950
He was the only survivor
of his family.

00:02:50.950 --> 00:02:53.920
And this gravestone
captured my attention

00:02:53.920 --> 00:02:58.270
so much it simply just
ignited this curiosity in me

00:02:58.270 --> 00:03:02.050
to know more about someone
who would be the one

00:03:02.050 --> 00:03:05.960
to change his name, and
pass as a Polish citizen.

00:03:05.960 --> 00:03:07.500
But it didn't end there.

00:03:07.500 --> 00:03:10.350
We went on a tour of
Krakow in the ghetto.

00:03:10.350 --> 00:03:12.280
And I found this picture.

00:03:12.280 --> 00:03:13.700
This is not cropped in.

00:03:13.700 --> 00:03:17.150
This is the actual picture I
took which was a huge mistake.

00:03:17.150 --> 00:03:19.990
And it talks about the
underground theaters.

00:03:19.990 --> 00:03:23.970
I'm a theater major so I
thought I wanted to know more

00:03:23.970 --> 00:03:25.840
about these underground
theaters.

00:03:25.840 --> 00:03:29.780
So I snapped the photo for
the only reason to go home

00:03:29.780 --> 00:03:31.080
and research it later.

00:03:31.080 --> 00:03:32.380
That was the mistake.

00:03:32.380 --> 00:03:33.680
I went home.

00:03:33.680 --> 00:03:35.750
I could not find
one single thing

00:03:35.750 --> 00:03:38.530
about the underground theaters.

00:03:38.530 --> 00:03:41.290
And the more I searched,
so I would search terms

00:03:41.290 --> 00:03:45.620
as Polish underground,
Jewish underground,

00:03:45.620 --> 00:03:55.370
Jewish underground Krakow,
and then I found my story.

00:03:55.370 --> 00:03:58.950
In doing the research for
"Resistance" it started

00:03:58.950 --> 00:04:02.370
with me reading as many books
as I could get my hands on,

00:04:02.370 --> 00:04:04.610
reading websites,
watching videos,

00:04:04.610 --> 00:04:07.100
looking at interviews
and diaries.

00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.010
And I came up with this.

00:04:09.010 --> 00:04:10.310
Just pages.

00:04:10.310 --> 00:04:12.910
I have 60 pages just of notes.

00:04:12.910 --> 00:04:14.210
Not the printouts.

00:04:14.210 --> 00:04:15.510
Just notes.

00:04:15.510 --> 00:04:18.070
And I thought there's
no way I can compile all

00:04:18.070 --> 00:04:19.370
of that information.

00:04:19.370 --> 00:04:22.070
So I thought, "I'm going
to make a timeline."

00:04:22.070 --> 00:04:25.430
So on the wall of my office you
see these six poster boards.

00:04:25.430 --> 00:04:29.180
They're color coded because
it turns out I'm super OCD.

00:04:29.180 --> 00:04:31.050
Didn't know that.

00:04:31.050 --> 00:04:35.380
But I started color coding
these just to give me a timeline

00:04:35.380 --> 00:04:36.690
of the highlights of the event.

00:04:36.690 --> 00:04:41.050
And that wasn't enough because
I was missing one thing.

00:04:41.050 --> 00:04:43.140
And the thing I was missing,
these were the dates.

00:04:43.140 --> 00:04:44.930
These were the facts.

00:04:44.930 --> 00:04:47.260
It wasn't the people.

00:04:47.260 --> 00:04:49.440
I needed the people.

00:04:49.440 --> 00:04:51.880
This poster board
sits very closest

00:04:51.880 --> 00:04:54.160
to where I would do my writing.

00:04:54.160 --> 00:04:59.470
These are the faces or those
who actually did the thing

00:04:59.470 --> 00:05:01.010
that I am writing about.

00:05:01.010 --> 00:05:04.510
These are the true heroes

00:05:04.510 --> 00:05:08.490
of the Jewish resistance
movement in Krakow, Poland.

00:05:08.490 --> 00:05:10.590
So let me tell you the story

00:05:10.590 --> 00:05:14.230
of the resistance
movement of Krakow, Poland.

00:05:14.230 --> 00:05:17.250
This is the history of the war.

00:05:17.250 --> 00:05:18.620
We have Poland.

00:05:18.620 --> 00:05:22.750
When the Germans invaded,
that was September 1, 1939.

00:05:22.750 --> 00:05:24.850
That was the start of the war.

00:05:24.850 --> 00:05:28.330
Germany floods across the
border in a blitzkrieg.

00:05:28.330 --> 00:05:33.250
It was an attack so massive that
the country of Poland collapsed.

00:05:33.250 --> 00:05:36.980
In 25 days, they
had surrendered.

00:05:36.980 --> 00:05:41.280
When the Germans moved
in, they said, "All right.

00:05:41.280 --> 00:05:44.380
Warsaw is the traditional
capital, but not for us.

00:05:44.380 --> 00:05:47.400
We're going to make
Krakow the capital

00:05:47.400 --> 00:05:48.700
of the general government."

00:05:48.700 --> 00:05:52.810
So to the Nazi empire
it will be Krakow.

00:05:52.810 --> 00:05:56.570
Because Krakow was the new
capital, they didn't want

00:05:56.570 --> 00:05:59.570
as many Jewish people in it.

00:05:59.570 --> 00:06:03.750
So they said, "15,000
can remain,

00:06:03.750 --> 00:06:06.480
and the rest have to leave."

00:06:06.480 --> 00:06:08.840
So who are you going
to keep in Krakow?

00:06:08.840 --> 00:06:13.930
Well, you can keep your
adults, and the children

00:06:13.930 --> 00:06:16.280
who are dependent upon them.

00:06:16.280 --> 00:06:19.780
There was one demographic
you didn't need there.

00:06:19.780 --> 00:06:21.890
Your teenagers.

00:06:21.890 --> 00:06:24.000
Teenagers largely
were sent away.

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:25.890
Now these teenagers
who were sent away,

00:06:25.890 --> 00:06:27.380
they'd never lived on their own.

00:06:27.380 --> 00:06:30.040
They were city kids
all of a sudden thrust

00:06:30.040 --> 00:06:32.360
in to the Polish countryside.

00:06:32.360 --> 00:06:34.030
But these were kids who --

00:06:34.030 --> 00:06:36.720
It wasn't just a
Polish countryside.

00:06:36.720 --> 00:06:40.610
It was full of Nazis,
and Polish citizens

00:06:40.610 --> 00:06:41.980
who were not sympathetic
to them.

00:06:41.980 --> 00:06:44.510
And these kids thought,
"Where will we go?"

00:06:44.510 --> 00:06:47.870
Well, they remembered,
"We have scout leaders."

00:06:47.870 --> 00:06:50.110
In the Jewish organizations
the scout was

00:06:50.110 --> 00:06:51.740
for the boys and the girls.

00:06:51.740 --> 00:06:54.020
And they remembered, "We
have these scout leaders,

00:06:54.020 --> 00:06:56.110
the Draengers [assumed
spelling].

00:06:56.110 --> 00:06:59.470
Shimshon Draenger [assumed
spelling] is a newspaper editor.

00:06:59.470 --> 00:07:00.990
He's 21 years old.

00:07:00.990 --> 00:07:04.570
His wife, Gusta,
is 20 years old.

00:07:04.570 --> 00:07:06.080
She's a housewife.

00:07:06.080 --> 00:07:08.860
And one by one these teenagers
show up at their home,

00:07:08.860 --> 00:07:11.540
and they say, "Can we
come in to your farm?"

00:07:11.540 --> 00:07:13.470
And the Draengers said, "Yes.

00:07:13.470 --> 00:07:15.330
Of course."

00:07:15.330 --> 00:07:19.210
For a while, the Draengers
were isolated from the war

00:07:19.210 --> 00:07:20.540
with the teenagers there,

00:07:20.540 --> 00:07:23.420
but bit by bit they started
hearing what's happening

00:07:23.420 --> 00:07:25.600
to their families
back in the ghettos.

00:07:25.600 --> 00:07:27.050
They hear about the actions.

00:07:27.050 --> 00:07:28.560
They hear about the deportments.

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:32.210
They hear about the
lineups in the streets.

00:07:32.210 --> 00:07:38.190
And these teenagers realize
that they have to make a choice.

00:07:38.190 --> 00:07:40.460
Choice number one.

00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.400
They do nothing.

00:07:42.400 --> 00:07:44.520
If they do nothing,
it is only a matter

00:07:44.520 --> 00:07:48.230
of time before they will die
on their knees to the Nazis.

00:07:48.230 --> 00:07:49.530
Choice number two.

00:07:49.530 --> 00:07:51.140
They will almost
certainly die as well,

00:07:51.140 --> 00:07:56.300
but they will die fighting back.

00:07:56.300 --> 00:08:00.290
In actual history one night
these teenagers sat around,

00:08:00.290 --> 00:08:02.450
and the Draengers
called for a vote.

00:08:02.450 --> 00:08:03.750
Who is in?

00:08:03.750 --> 00:08:07.340
And, one by one, these
teenagers' hands went up.

00:08:07.340 --> 00:08:10.170
Now one of the jobs they
needed these teenagers

00:08:10.170 --> 00:08:12.480
to do was the job of a courier.

00:08:12.480 --> 00:08:15.630
The job of a courier was
to go to the ghetto gates.

00:08:15.630 --> 00:08:16.930
The ghettos were sealed.

00:08:16.930 --> 00:08:19.650
No Jewish people in or out.

00:08:19.650 --> 00:08:22.300
And so it was a way
of isolating them.

00:08:22.300 --> 00:08:25.740
They needed a teenager to
go to the ghetto gates,

00:08:25.740 --> 00:08:27.870
look that Nazi officer
in the eye,

00:08:27.870 --> 00:08:31.800
and convince him
that she is Jewish.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:35.160
On her back she is
smuggling food,

00:08:35.160 --> 00:08:40.850
information, money, and weapons.

00:08:40.850 --> 00:08:43.870
She knows it is likely that
one day she will be caught,

00:08:43.870 --> 00:08:46.420
and if she is, she has
sworn never to give

00:08:46.420 --> 00:08:50.180
up any information
about the resistance.

00:08:50.180 --> 00:08:54.680
Who are you going
to use to do that?

00:08:54.680 --> 00:08:59.930
No males. Because of
circumcision, you cannot do it.

00:08:59.930 --> 00:09:01.380
No mothers.

00:09:01.380 --> 00:09:03.360
They have children or
they have work duty.

00:09:03.360 --> 00:09:05.160
It only gives you
one demographic,

00:09:05.160 --> 00:09:07.580
and that was your teenage girls.

00:09:07.580 --> 00:09:12.240
In actual history, girls
15, 16, 17 years old,

00:09:12.240 --> 00:09:14.930
that is what they would
do, face that Nazi officer,

00:09:14.930 --> 00:09:16.980
talk her way inside the ghetto.

00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:19.300
Once she gets inside,
it is her job

00:09:19.300 --> 00:09:23.030
to convince the Jewish
people she is one of them

00:09:23.030 --> 00:09:26.070
because most likely she
will be smuggling someone

00:09:26.070 --> 00:09:30.150
out to a safe house.

00:09:30.150 --> 00:09:33.120
This resistance movement
that grew from the couriers

00:09:33.120 --> 00:09:35.520
in Krakow was known as Akiba,

00:09:35.520 --> 00:09:40.100
named after a Jewish
rabbi from biblical times.

00:09:40.100 --> 00:09:48.010
And Akiba conducted a raid
that was all across Krakow.

00:09:48.010 --> 00:09:52.130
As a result of the
raid, the Draengers --

00:09:53.440 --> 00:09:55.550
Shimshon was arrested.

00:09:55.550 --> 00:09:57.410
His wife gave herself up.

00:09:57.410 --> 00:09:58.730
That was a pact they had made.

00:09:58.730 --> 00:10:02.160
Whatever happens to one of us,
the other of us will follow.

00:10:02.160 --> 00:10:04.720
The Draengers were sent
to Montelupich prison.

00:10:04.720 --> 00:10:09.010
Montelupich was the
worst of the worst.

00:10:09.010 --> 00:10:13.060
The Nazis started
with her, with Gusta.

00:10:13.060 --> 00:10:15.550
And this is why it's important.

00:10:15.550 --> 00:10:21.700
This book right here is -- It
is called "Justyna's Narrative."

00:10:21.700 --> 00:10:24.050
Justyna is Gusta's code name.

00:10:24.050 --> 00:10:26.330
That's the name she went by.

00:10:26.330 --> 00:10:28.170
This book isn't in
print anymore.

00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:30.820
If you were to see this
in a used bookstore,

00:10:30.820 --> 00:10:32.780
most likely you'd pass this up.

00:10:32.780 --> 00:10:34.980
Nothing interesting about this.

00:10:34.980 --> 00:10:39.820
I'm going to tell you about this
book's importance in history.

00:10:39.820 --> 00:10:42.470
The Nazis started with Gusta.

00:10:42.470 --> 00:10:45.750
They absolutely tortured her.

00:10:45.750 --> 00:10:48.970
And when they had done it,
and Gusta refused to give

00:10:48.970 --> 00:10:51.630
up a single word
about the resistance,

00:10:51.630 --> 00:10:54.200
then they bring her husband in.

00:10:54.200 --> 00:10:55.830
They brought Shimshon in.

00:10:55.830 --> 00:10:57.930
Now those of you
who are husbands,

00:10:57.930 --> 00:11:01.210
or if you have a
husband, you know how far

00:11:01.210 --> 00:11:04.770
that man will go to
protect his wife.

00:11:04.770 --> 00:11:09.270
And he comes in, and he sees
what the Nazis have done to her.

00:11:09.270 --> 00:11:13.350
And he's ready to do whatever
he needs to save his wife,

00:11:13.350 --> 00:11:17.720
but Gusta looks at her husband
and she says, "Look at this.

00:11:17.720 --> 00:11:21.990
They did their worst
to me, and I'm fine.

00:11:21.990 --> 00:11:24.590
Don't tell them anything."

00:11:24.590 --> 00:11:28.310
And she is the one who upholds
the secret of the resistance.

00:11:28.310 --> 00:11:31.770
They take her back to her
cell in Montelupich prison.

00:11:31.770 --> 00:11:36.630
There's other women there also
from Akiba who were arrested.

00:11:36.630 --> 00:11:38.840
Gusta, they'd broken
the bones of her hands.

00:11:38.840 --> 00:11:40.670
So she cannot write.

00:11:40.670 --> 00:11:43.520
But she starts to
dictate her story.

00:11:43.520 --> 00:11:46.460
Five women are taking
the dictation.

00:11:46.460 --> 00:11:49.840
They're writing it down
on strips of toilet paper.

00:11:49.840 --> 00:11:52.230
They sew the strips of
toilet paper together

00:11:52.230 --> 00:11:54.220
with a thread from
their dresses.

00:11:54.220 --> 00:11:56.750
They had one needle in the
cell, and they would share it

00:11:56.750 --> 00:11:59.480
to sew these toilet
paper pieces together.

00:11:59.480 --> 00:12:01.810
They then smuggled
out as much --

00:12:01.810 --> 00:12:04.380
They smuggled out
all five copies,

00:12:04.380 --> 00:12:08.810
hoping that at least something
would safely get through.

00:12:08.810 --> 00:12:13.120
This book is what
Gusta Draenger narrated

00:12:13.120 --> 00:12:14.800
from Montelupich prison.

00:12:14.800 --> 00:12:17.690
We have all but one
and a half chapters

00:12:17.690 --> 00:12:19.820
of her record of
this resistance.

00:12:19.820 --> 00:12:23.960
This is the reason we
know it even existed.

00:12:23.960 --> 00:12:28.290
This is the only reason we
know what these teenagers

00:12:28.290 --> 00:12:32.760
accomplished here is
because of Gusta Draenger.

00:12:32.760 --> 00:12:36.660
Now in this book, in
"Resistance," I'm going

00:12:36.660 --> 00:12:41.140
to follow two Jewish
couriers from Krakow ghettos.

00:12:41.140 --> 00:12:43.900
I'm going to follow them up to
Lodz [assumed spelling] ghetto

00:12:43.900 --> 00:12:45.540
in the center of Poland.

00:12:45.540 --> 00:12:49.230
Lodz was the worst of
the worst of the ghettos.

00:12:49.230 --> 00:12:51.630
It was a horrible,
horrible place.

00:12:51.630 --> 00:12:54.260
And then by spring
of 1943 I'm going

00:12:54.260 --> 00:12:58.090
to bring these two
couriers in to Warsaw.

00:12:58.090 --> 00:13:01.610
Warsaw ghetto was the
largest of the ghettos.

00:13:01.610 --> 00:13:07.340
In January of 1943, the Nazis
entered with a plan to remove

00:13:07.340 --> 00:13:12.570
as many as 300,000 Jewish
people in to the death camps.

00:13:12.570 --> 00:13:14.800
The Jewish people fought back.

00:13:14.800 --> 00:13:18.550
And, in fact, chased the
Nazis out of the ghettos.

00:13:18.550 --> 00:13:21.510
But they knew it was
only a matter of time

00:13:21.510 --> 00:13:22.990
that the Nazis would come back.

00:13:22.990 --> 00:13:26.630
And, when they came back,
they would come back in force.

00:13:26.630 --> 00:13:28.850
So they began to prepare.

00:13:28.850 --> 00:13:34.360
By spring of 1943, this man, his
name is Mordechai Anielewicz.

00:13:34.360 --> 00:13:37.780
He was 21 years old at
the beginning of the war.

00:13:37.780 --> 00:13:39.940
He was a career counselor.

00:13:39.940 --> 00:13:41.900
No military background.

00:13:41.900 --> 00:13:47.450
This man organized Jewish
civilians in an uprising

00:13:47.450 --> 00:13:49.690
against the Nazi army.

00:13:49.690 --> 00:13:52.760
On the night before Passover,

00:13:52.760 --> 00:13:56.500
an announcement went throughout
the Jewish population trapped

00:13:56.500 --> 00:13:59.120
inside the ghetto, and it said,

00:13:59.120 --> 00:14:03.620
"The Nazis have our
ghetto surrounded."

00:14:03.620 --> 00:14:07.810
And on Passover morning
it would begin.

00:14:07.810 --> 00:14:10.930
Mordechai Anielewicz would
lead Jewish civilians,

00:14:10.930 --> 00:14:14.820
about 450 of them, against
the entire Nazi army.

00:14:14.820 --> 00:14:16.120
This is a picture of one

00:14:16.120 --> 00:14:20.240
of the Jewish fighters
from the rooftops.

00:14:20.240 --> 00:14:23.800
They survived longer
against the Nazi army

00:14:23.800 --> 00:14:27.740
than the entire country of
Poland lasted against the Nazis.

00:14:27.740 --> 00:14:32.330
It was always clear how
the story was going to end,

00:14:32.330 --> 00:14:36.470
but for the Jewish people,
this was their victory

00:14:36.470 --> 00:14:38.200
because in this moment
they said,

00:14:38.200 --> 00:14:41.430
"It doesn't matter
what our end is.

00:14:41.430 --> 00:14:44.410
It matters that we
chose our end.

00:14:44.410 --> 00:14:45.750
We chose this.

00:14:45.750 --> 00:14:49.690
And we did not go
down on our knees."

00:14:49.690 --> 00:14:54.450
The theme of resistance
is best stated this way.

00:14:54.450 --> 00:14:57.980
This comes from the
afterward of the book.

00:14:57.980 --> 00:15:00.840
It says, "May we never forget.

00:15:00.840 --> 00:15:03.510
May we live with
honor at all times,

00:15:03.510 --> 00:15:06.500
regardless of our circumstances.

00:15:06.500 --> 00:15:08.590
And may we choose love, a weapon

00:15:08.590 --> 00:15:12.540
that will defeat hate
every single time

00:15:12.540 --> 00:15:16.700
because love is the resistance."

00:15:16.700 --> 00:15:20.540
This book deals with what
the Nazis decided to do

00:15:20.540 --> 00:15:23.900
about the so-called
Jewish problem.

00:15:23.900 --> 00:15:28.180
And we live in a world right now
where you can see the recyclings

00:15:28.180 --> 00:15:33.870
of hate and anger and name
calling and isolation.

00:15:33.870 --> 00:15:38.840
And if we respond to that
with hate, and anger,

00:15:38.840 --> 00:15:41.310
and name calling, and isolation,

00:15:41.310 --> 00:15:44.220
we are feeding in
to the problem.

00:15:44.220 --> 00:15:51.180
If we wish to be a solution,
the resistance is love.

