00:19:16.390 --> 00:19:18.810
&gt;&gt; Speaker 3: How did
you decide to make "Mark

00:19:18.810 --> 00:19:21.780
of the Thief" take
place in Rome?

00:19:21.780 --> 00:19:23.180
&gt;&gt; Jennifer A Nielsen:
"Mark of the Thief" always.

00:19:23.180 --> 00:19:25.410
"Mark of the Thief" is
ancient Rome with magic.

00:19:25.410 --> 00:19:27.040
It always had to take place.

00:19:27.040 --> 00:19:29.470
And it's because of
two facts I knew.

00:19:29.470 --> 00:19:30.770
Number one.

00:19:30.770 --> 00:19:34.230
That every Roman child who was a
citizen would have worn a bulla,

00:19:34.230 --> 00:19:35.530
that amulet.

00:19:35.530 --> 00:19:38.270
And I just thought
that was kind of cool,

00:19:38.270 --> 00:19:40.990
but I knew fact number
two, that Julius Caesar

00:19:40.990 --> 00:19:44.280
in actual history used to
tell the people he had come

00:19:44.280 --> 00:19:45.580
from the gods.

00:19:45.580 --> 00:19:47.980
So he would be like, "Oh,
Venus, that you all worship?

00:19:47.980 --> 00:19:49.700
Yeah. That's my grandma."

00:19:49.700 --> 00:19:52.330
Right? And I thought, "Well,

00:19:52.330 --> 00:19:54.940
what if Caesar was
telling the truth?"

00:19:54.940 --> 00:19:56.820
If he really had
come from the gods,

00:19:56.820 --> 00:19:59.380
Julius Caesar would
have been a demigod.

00:19:59.380 --> 00:20:03.770
And what if his magic was kept
in his bulla that becomes lost

00:20:03.770 --> 00:20:06.930
after his death and
remains lost for 200 years?

00:20:06.930 --> 00:20:09.060
So it always had
to be ancient Rome

00:20:09.060 --> 00:20:11.910
because of Caesar and the bulla.

00:20:11.910 --> 00:20:13.210
Fantastic.

00:20:13.210 --> 00:20:14.510
Thank you.

